                                historical sights. However, the network is limited to certain parts of the city. Tram
                                rides are very affordable.
                            </p>
                            <img src="~/img/alex_tram.jpeg" alt="alex_tram">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info" data-count="2">
                        <div class="items">
                            <p>
                                Alexandria is connected to other cities in Egypt by rail. There are two main stations:
                                Sidi Gaber Station provides service to Cairo, while Misr Station connects Alexandria to
                                cities in the Nile Delta region. The rail network is a convenient way to travel longer
                                distances, though still basic.
                            </p>
                            <img src="~/img/alex_train.jpeg" alt="alex_train">
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="info" data-count="3">
                        <div class="items">
                            <p>
                                taxis are a popular way for both locals and tourists to get around Alexandria. You can
                                hail taxis on the street or hire one from designated taxi stands throughout the city.
